text: Finnia Wunram (born 18 December 1995) is a German swimmer, specialising in open water events. She competed in the women's 10 km and 25 km events at the 2019 World Aquatics Championships, winning a silver medal in the latter. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1995 births Category:Living people Category:German female swimmers Category:Female freestyle swimmers Category:People from Eckernförde Category:World Aquatics Championships medalists in open water swimming Category:Female long-distance swimmers
